  "markup": "\u003Cp\u003ERheumatological disorders such as rheumatoid arthritis, osteoarthritis, lupus and scleroderma cause pain, swelling, and stiffness in patients. Low-level laser therapy (LLLT) or photobiomodulation (PBM) is well-known for its efficacy in managing arthritis symptoms. What are the best parameters for applying laser therapy to patients with rheumatological disorders to manage pain and deliver superior outcomes?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EIn this webinar, Drs. Christopher Carraway and Timothy Demchak will explore using photobiomodulation for managing autoimmune rheumatological diseases. They will discuss how laser therapy provides drug-free pain relief, reduces swelling around joints, and increases joint mobility to enhance quality of life in rheumatological disease patients.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003EKey Talking Points\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n    \u003Cli\u003EReview the research to understand how PBM functions in relieving pain, reducing inflammation, increasing range of motion and more in treating rheumatological disorder\u003C/li\u003E\n    \u003Cli\u003EHow to develop protocols and determine dosage for treating diseases such as rheumatoid arthritis and osteoarthritis\u003C/li\u003E\n    \u003Cli\u003EReal-world cases showing the application of PBM for managing common rheumatological disorders\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E"
}]]></Value>
    </description>
